SCP-9009.WET-CARDBOARD "Joseph R. Biden," former deputy of .OREO-UCAV, was chosen as YAKUB's premier presidential nominee, as a more moderate alternative to the incautious aggression of the .HAPPY-ACCIDENT presidency. .WET-CARDBOARD was inserted into the presidential race as the Democratic nominee, running against .HAPPY-ACCIDENT. Once again, the executive decision was made to avoid interfering with election results, in order to facilitate the democratic process.



Inconveniently, .WET-CARDBOARD had been retired since 2017, due to accrued cognitive decay. Specialized teams were dispatched to the Site-98 storage morgue to restore the instance using [[[SCP-427]]]. However, due to unforseen interactions between SCP-427 and SCP-9009 biology, .WET-CARDBOARD retained significantly decreased cognitive faculties following revival.[[footnote]]Research into what cognitive faculties (if any) existed prior is ongoing.[[/footnote]] Despite this impairment, .WET-CARDBOARD secured the presidency in 2020 November, defeating .HAPPY-ACCIDENT. 



